  "text": "# Chromium Multi-Process Architecture Key Files\n\nThe Chromium multi-process architecture is defined across several critical C++ source files and Mojo interface definitions:\n\n## 1. RenderProcessHostImpl (Browser-side Renderer Representation)\n**Files:** `content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h` and `.cc`\n**Class:** `RenderProcessHostImpl` (line 195 in header)\n**Purpose:** Represents the browser-side view of a renderer process. This class inherits from `RenderProcessHost` and manages the communication channel between the browser process and individual renderer processes. It handles IPC routing, resource management, and coordination with the Mojo IPC system.\n\n## 2. BrowserMainLoop (Main Browser Process Event Loop)\n**Files:** `content/browser/browser_main_loop.h` and `.cc`\n**Class:** `BrowserMainLoop` (line 106 in header)\n**Purpose:** Implements the main browser process event loop and stages called from `BrowserMainRunner`. It initializes and manages critical browser subsystems including the UI thread, IO thread, media services, and other core browser infrastructure.\n\n## 3. RenderThreadImpl (Renderer Process Main Thread)\n**Files:** `content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h` and `.cc`\n**Class:** `RenderThreadImpl` (defined in header)\n**Purpose:** Represents the main thread of a renderer process where `blink::WebView` instances live. It inherits from `RenderThread`, `ChildThreadImpl`, `mojom::Renderer`, and `viz::mojom::CompositingModeWatcher`. This class routes IPC messages to the appropriate `RenderFrameImpl` instances based on routing IDs.\n\n## 4. ChildProcessLauncher (Child Process Spawner)\n**Files:** `content/browser/child_process_launcher.h` and `.cc`\n**Class:** `ChildProcessLauncher` (line 212 in header)\n**Purpose:** Responsible for asynchronously launching child processes (renderers, GPU process, utility processes, etc.). It avoids blocking the main thread during OS process creation and notifies clients when the process